  "texts": [
    "Page 31 of 38 86",
    "In addition, the challenge with earlier AI models is the lack of explainability, as they are often seen as 'black boxes' that do not provide explanations of how their predictions were made.",
    "This drawback makes it difficult to trust the decisions made by AI.",
    "Moreover, there are ethical considerations related to patient consent when participating in studies that employ unexplainable AI algorithms.",
    "To overcome these challenges, Explainable AI, XAI, has been developed (Mitchell et al. 1986)."
  ]
}